http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Tiruchirapalli/Save-and-educate-girl-child/article14019409.ece

Under the auspices of Directorate of Field Publicity, an outreach programme on ‘Save and educate girl child’ was organised at Pallapuram village panchayat near here recently.Firoze Mohideen, Senior Superintendent of Post Offices, spoke on ‘Sukanya Samriddhi Yojana’ and ‘Atal Pension Yojana’. M. Annadurai, Regional Director, Directorate of Field Publicity, said that the programme also aimed at creating awareness about ‘Swacch Bharat Abhiyan’ and ‘Prime Minister’s Jan Dhan Yojana’ scheme.Later, Shanthi, Principal, District Institute of Education and Training, flagged off an awareness rally in which students of DIET and public participated. Mathivanan, Pallapuram village panchayat president, spoke on the steps taken by the panchayat for enrolling girls into schools.TMC meetingCadre of the Tamil Manila Congress in the central region, at a meeting held here recently, have urged their leader G.K. Vasan to contest from Ariyalur Assembly segment during the forthcoming elections to the Assembly. Farmers’ representatives and party workers from Nagapattinam, Tiruvarur, Tiruchi, Thanjavur, Perambalur and Ariyalur participated in the meeting. The meeting, in a resolution, urged the Public Works Department to initiate steps for construction of check dams at places like Tirumazhapadi, Sengaraiyur and Sullankudi for harvesting storm water presently let off into sea. T.K.S. Kailasam, vice president of the Farmers wing of the party, A. Nagarajan its state president and S.R.M. Kumar, Ariyalur district president, spoke.